article.description: — Jamaree Bouyea tied his career high with 24 points as San Francisco beat San Diego 70-62 on Thursday.
article.headline: Bouyea leads San Francisco over San Diego 70-62
article.linkText: Bouyea leads San Francisco over San Diego 70-62
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- — Jamaree Bouyea tied his career high with 24 points as San Francisco beat San Diego 70-62 on Thursday. The game marked the West Coast Conference opener for both teams. Josh Kunen and Dzmitry Ryuny combined for 17 pointws and 16 rebounds for San Francisco (7-4). Josh Parrish had 15 points and eight rebounds for the Toreros (1-4). Joey Calcaterra added 14 points. Yauhen Massalski had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
